{
  "id": "MGASA-2015-0050",
  "summary": "Updated hexchat packages fix security vulnerability",
  "details": "HexChat did not verify that the server hostname matched the domain name in \nthe subject's Common Name (CN) or subjectAltName field in X.509 \ncertificates. This could allow a man-in-the-middle attacker to spoof an \nSSL server if they had a certificate that was valid for any domain name.\n",
